                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                <head>183. Telegram From [<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>] to
                    Operation <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> Headquarters in
                        Florida<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d183fn1">Source: Central
                        Intelligence Agency, Job 79–01025A, Box 13, Folder 6. Secret; RYBAT; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>. Repeated to the Director of
                        Central Intelligence.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>[<hi rend="italic">place not declassified</hi>], <date
                        calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-14T22:33:00+00:00">June 14, 1954,
                        2233Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>583. 1. SECANT and all others adamant that 1 bomb, placed on presidential palace
                    would be convincer to army on-the-fencers and cause mass hiding of key
                    opposition.</p>
                <p>2. Pilots convinced palace can be hit on 1 shot. SECANT convinced people would
                    understand 1 bomb only not meant for them and would be convinced we holding back
                    on bombing to prevent harming them. Field convinced.</p>
                <p>3. Request SOMERSET be advised in accord with <persName>LINCOLN</persName>
                    decision. If used, should be timed hours after clandestine broadcast announces
                    go.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
